entries.femaleVariant: Hello, V. Please, come in.
Good to see ya, V.
Got a decent picture of what went down.
It's not a hundred percent clear what happened…
entries.maleVariant: It's not a hundred percent clear what happened.

entries.femaleVariant: Hardly anything ever is, but...?
There was an accident, embarrassing one. Rhyne died at a sex club. Was prolly too much for 'im.
Nobody there helping him? To leave this world, vacate his seat?
Thanks for your help, V.
Case is pretty complex, leaves a lotta questions unanswered. I'd rather not draw any conclusions yet.
But you must have an opinion.
Think Weldon Holt was behind Rhyne's death.
entries.maleVariant: I think Weldon Holt was behind Rhyne's death.

entries.femaleVariant: Yeah, I got some idea.
Rhyne was murdered. At a sex club. Someone gave him a virus-spiked BD.
You sure?
Please, have a seat.
Elizabeth tells me you have answers for us. I'm all ears.
It was an accident. NCPD covered it up.
Holt's behind it.
Rhyne was murdered by BD.
Ya ask me – no.
What a relief. That's good to know.
So why'd they lie...? Eh, never mind, don't answer. I know why. Dull death, dull case…
Can't draw any real conclusions.
Jeff, honey… read between the lines.
The case is complicated? But dying at home of a cardiac malfunction – that's not complicated.
So we were right?
Yes. And that's enough for me. We have to be careful. Very careful, Jeff.
That's what V's trying to tell us.
But my wife's right. We will sleep better.
Your fee…
Same BD almost wiped me, so... yeah, I'd say I'm sure.
entries.maleVariant: Same BD almost wiped me. So yeah, I'd say I'm sure.

entries.femaleVariant: Got any idea who did it?
Weldon Holt.
No, no idea.
Police are on it.
Can't say for sure, but... a lotta things point to Weldon Holt.
entries.maleVariant: Can't say for sure... but a lotta things point to Weldon Holt.

entries.femaleVariant: That I didn't manage to figure out.
Cops are working the case again. Investigation into Rhyne's death will be reopened.
entries.maleVariant: Cops are workin' the case again. Investigation into Rhyne's death will be reopened.

entries.femaleVariant: I knew it! You got any proof?
I don't. Just... strong suspicions.
entries.maleVariant: I don't. Just, uh… strong suspicions.

entries.femaleVariant: That's all we need to know, Jeff. We have to be careful. Keep a close eye on Holt. And up our security.
You're right... As always, you're right.
I see. Either way, you risked your life.
That's enough information for us. More than enough.
That's very good news. I feel… calmed.
Just gonna tell you one thing.
What's that?
Something tells me it'll be more than one.
Prolly gonna be more than one, but all right.
entries.maleVariant: Prob'ly gonna be more than one... Hmph, but all right.

entries.femaleVariant: I'm listenin'.
Don't tell 'em nothin'. Don't get involved. This muck is deeper than ya think.
Suck you in if you're not careful.
Don't be dramatic.
I'm always careful.
They won't pay me if I don't tell them something.
Chill on the drama. My role in this ends here.
I'm always careful.
If I don't give 'em somethin', they're not gonna pay me.
Fine, do whatever the fuck you want. Not like ya listen anyway.
We'll manage without that.
There's no sense in which you gotta eat.
Make yourself at home. Jefferson will join us shortly.
[Sit] Thanks.
Thank you.
[Stand] Glad I could help.
Glad I could help.
[Stand] Watch out for each other.
You two watch out for each other.
And the conference? Did you manage, will we be in City Hall?
No, no, no! Jeff was a councilperson until very recently. He has just as much of a right to use that space as Rhyne.
Get it done. Today. We are not push-overs, we are not going away. The conference will be at City Hall.
You helped us, V. Thank you. But we'll call if... we need anything.
